headline: Indian fintech firm Pine Labs' $440 million IPO subscribed on final day
summary: The share sale happened in the middle of a wave of listings with the IPO market set ‌to top last year's record.  Pine Labs, backed by Peak XV Partners, Temasek, PayPal and ⁠Mastercard, provides payment solutions ‌such as point-of-sale terminals, and competes with Paytm and Walmart-owned PhonePe.  Qualified institutional buyers led the bidding for Pine Labs shares, ​with subscriptions at 2.14 times the shares reserved for them.
